src="https://connect.facebook.net/en_GB/sdk.js#xfbml=1&amp;version=v21.0"></script> <div class="fb-post" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/keithcaceres314/posts/pfbid02BuhiJ8eX9Ec3q93Tq5nfWU9kNYsZ1GA5MFyFddGwTZcQQCJvUZq7rx9e5DA6kZ3hl" data-width="500" data-show-text="true"> <blockquote cite="https://www.facebook.com/keithcaceres314/posts/10235405823269287" class="fb-xfbml-parse-ignore"> <p>Our guest speaker for our September 5th (7:30 PM &#064; The Dale Etheridge Planetarium at the College of Southern Nevada)...</p> Posted by <a href="#" role="button">Keith Caceres</a> on&nbsp;<a href="https://www.facebook.com/keithcaceres314/posts/10235405823269287">Tuesday 13 August 2024</a> </blockquote> </div> </div> <h3 id="dale-etheridge-planetarium-at-the-college-of-southern-nevada">Dale Etheridge Planetarium at the College of Southern Nevada</h3> <swiper-container keyboard="true" navigation="true" pagination="true" pagination-clickable="true" pagination-dynamic-bullets="true" rewind="true"> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_1.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_2-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_2.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_3-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_3-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_3-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_3.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_4-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_4-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_4-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_4.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_5-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_5-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_5-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/LVAS_Meeting_5.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> </swiper-container> <div class="caption"> Images captured from the event. </div> <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; margin: 10px 0;"> <div style="position: relative; width: 100%; max-width: 800px; padding-top: 75%; overflow: hidden;"> <iframe src="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1BWhanJRXZOOJah_ergGiUlstaxTZQaay/preview" style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;" allow="autoplay" frameborder="0"> </iframe> </div> <div class="caption" style="text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;"> Short clip from the event describing gravitational waves (GW) and the current ground-based GW detector network. </div> </div> <style>iframe{max-width:100%}@media(max-width:600px){iframe{width:100%;height:auto}}</style> <p>It was a pleasure meeting Ty Hummon (on my left) and Aly (on my right), and a joy reconnecting with Marcus (back row, right) and Keith Caceres (far right). We delved into fascinating discussions about gravitational waves, next-generation GW detectors, gravitation, relativity, and even indulged in some entertaining Sci-Fi debates.</p> <div style="display: flex; justify-content: center; flex-direction: column; align-items: center; margin: 10px 0;"> <div id="fb-root"></div> <script async="" defer="" crossorigin="anonymous" src="https://connect.facebook.net/en_GB/sdk.js#xfbml=1&amp;version=v21.0"></script> <div class="fb-post" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/summonhummon/posts/pfbid02BHE6SSZo4qsbrdoVjgsmqD47D2ubwwVnxPHY2Hevbfxvtgnwdf2mmR7MD2QEvpaMl" data-width="500" data-show-text="true"> <blockquote cite="https://www.facebook.com/summonhummon/posts/10231999839246470" class="fb-xfbml-parse-ignore"> <p>Me, Aly, Marcus, and Keith Caceres <br/> September Meeting with Rachel Langgin working on her Ph.D<br/> <a href="http://www.lvastronomy.org" target="_blank">www.lvastronomy.org</a><br/> </p> Posted by <a href="https://www.facebook.com/summonhummon">Ty Hummon</a> on&nbsp; <a href="https://www.facebook.com/summonhummon/posts/10231999839246470">Saturday 7 September 2024</a> </blockquote> </div> </div> <p>It was inspiring to connect with a group of amateur astronomers enthusiastic about discussing high-energy astrophysics, even amidst the light pollution of my hometown. I look forward to future collaborations with the LVAS!</p>]]></content><author><name>Rachel Langgin</name></author><category term="public-outreach"/><category term="presentations"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[This September, I was estactic to be welcomed back as the guest speaker for the Las Vegas Astronomical Society‚Äôs monthly meeting. Check out the event here!]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Stargazing Event at Mt. Chareston</title><link href="https://rachellanggin.com/blog/2024/mtcharleston/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Stargazing Event at Mt. Chareston"/><published>2024-08-06T01:59:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-08-06T01:59:00+00:00</updated><id>https://rachellanggin.com/blog/2024/mtcharleston</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://rachellanggin.com/blog/2024/mtcharleston/"><![CDATA[<p>This summer, I was honored to be the guest speaker for the Las Vegas Astronomical Society‚Äôs stargazing event at the Spring Mountain Visitor Gateway at Mount Charleston. As a Las Vegas local, I fondly remember going to Mt. Charleston as a child for Girl Scout sleep-away camp, so I eagerly embraced the opportunity to discuss gravitational waves with other local families. Below are some photos and a video of the event!</p> <h2 id="amphitheatre-at-spring-mountain-visitor-gateway">Amphitheatre at Spring Mountain Visitor Gateway</h2> <p>Thank you to Keith Caceres for capturing these images.</p> <swiper-container keyboard="true" navigation="true" pagination="true" pagination-clickable="true" pagination-dynamic-bullets="true" rewind="true"> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/MtC_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/MtC_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/MtC_1-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/MtC_1.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </swiper-slide> <swiper-slide> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/MtC_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/MtC_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/MtC_2-1400.webp 1400w," type="image/webp" sizes="95vw"/> <img src="/assets/img/MtC_2.jpeg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.re